{{short description|2011 book by Sean J. McGrath}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = The Dark Ground of Spirit: Schelling and the Unconscious | image = | caption = | authors = [[Sean McGrath (philosopher)|Sean J. McGrath]] | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[philosophy of psychology]] | publisher = [[Routledge]] | pub_date = 2011 | media_type = Print ([[Paperback]]) | pages = 232 pp. | isbn = 9780415492126 }}
'''''The Dark Ground of Spirit: Schelling and the Unconscious''''' is a 2011 book by [[Sean McGrath (philosopher)|Sean J. McGrath]], in which the author examines how the [[psychoanalytical]] concept of [[the unconscious]] originates in [[German Idealism]], especially the work of the German philosopher, [[Friedrich Schelling]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=McGrath |first1=S. J. |title=The Dark Ground of Spirit: Schelling and the Unconscious |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Dark_Ground_of_Spirit.html?id=tJHObwAACAAJ |publisher=Routledge |accessdate=22 October 2018 |language=en |date=2012}}</ref>
==Reception== ''The Dark Ground of Spirit'' has been reviewed by [[David Tacey]], Benjamin Burger and J. A. F. Marshall.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Marshall |first1=J.A.F. |title=S.J. McGrath, The Dark Ground of Spirit |url=https://www.c-scp.org/2014/09/03/s-j-mcgrath-the-dark-ground-of-spirit |website=[[Australasian Society for Continental Philosophy]] |accessdate=9 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Berger |first1=Benjamin |title=McGrath S. J. The Dark Ground of Spirit: Schelling and the Unconscious. Routledge, 2012. ISBN 978-0-4154-9212-6 (pbk). Pp. 232. |journal=[[Hegel Bulletin]] |date=May 2014 |volume=35 |issue=1 |pages=152–158 |doi=10.1017/hgl.2014.14 |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/hegel-bulletin/article/s-jmcgraththe-dark-ground-of-spirit-schelling-and-the-unconscious-routledge-2012-isbn-978-0-4154-9212-6-pbk-pp-232/D1D8B6132E32E275DCFDFF5B7A5C7D2A |accessdate=3 September 2018 |language=en |issn=2051-5367}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Tacey |first1=David |title=The dark ground of spirit: Schelling and the unconscious/The foundations of the unconscious: Schelling, Freud and the birth of the modern psyche |journal=[[International Journal of Jungian Studies]] |date=October 2013 |volume=5 |issue=3 |pages=267–270 |doi=10.1080/19409052.2013.814408 |url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/19409052.2013.814408 |accessdate=3 September 2018 |language=en |issn=1940-9052}}</ref>
