'''Uladzimir Konan''' (born 1934, Hrodna, Belarus; d. 6 June 2011) was a [[Belarus]]ian [[philosophy|philosopher]].<ref>[http://naviny.by/rubrics/english/2011/06/06/ic_news_259_369392/ Prominent philosopher Uladzimir Konan dies at 77]</ref><ref>[http://www.democraticbelarus.eu/node/12717 Prominent philosopher Uladzimir Konan dies at 77]</ref>  He was born in the [[Hrodna]] region of Belarus. He graduated from [[Belarusian State University]]'s History faculty and worked with the Institute of Philosophy and Law of the [[Belarusian National Academy of Sciences]].

